{title: Ninety Nine Year Blues}
{artist: Hank Snow}
{composer: Written by Jimmie Rodgers and Roy E. Hall}

[C]Lawd these ninety nine blues ain't no fancy dream
If [G7]you had two lives to live you'd know just what I [C]mean
When the judge read the verdict it nearly knocked me down
Said [G7]boy you got two six's they're all upside [C]down
It ain't the days I've been here it's the days I got to stay
All [G7]the old friends I ever had done shook hands and gone [C]away
My good gal told me the day I hit this can
You've [G7]made your bed in sorrow now sleep on it like a [C]man
Ninety nine and ninety nine make one hundred and ninety eight
That's [G7]four years pretty normal than you can figure up on your [C]slate
I don't know what else is in the world to lose
Cause [G7]I've lost everything except these ninety nine [C]blues